kernel_variant.question:
Fix an integer $n\ge 2$.  
Find, with proof, all real-valued functions  

  $g:[0,\infty)\longrightarrow[0,\infty)$  

that are continuous on $[0,\infty)$ and strictly positive on $(0,\infty)$ and satisfy, for every $x>0$,  

\[
\boxed{\;
\int_{0}^{x}\frac1{\,n+1\,}\,t^{\,n-1}\,g^{2}(t)\,dt
\;=\;
\frac1{x^{\,n}}\Bigl(\,\int_{0}^{x}t^{\,n-1}\,g(t)\,dt\Bigr)^{2}
\;}
\tag{\star }
\]

(When $n=1$ this reduces to the original B-4 identity after the change of variables used in the current kernel variant, but here the weight $t^{\,n-1}$ corresponds to the $(n\!+\!1)$-dimensional solid of revolution whose centroid condition generalises the original one.)

